== Kickback

=== Set trumps if possible

If we can make a forcing bid that sets a #major suit# as
trump, then we must do that before we can use kickback.

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
|  1S  |  2H  ||
| !2S! |  ?   || 2S = only 5*{S}
|      |  3S  || sets trump = {S}
|      |  4S  || to play
|      | 4NT  || natural, 18-19 HCP
|===

****
The rule doesn't apply for minors because we use optional-minorwood
in many cases.

_e.g._ After an uncontested 1H{ndash}2D, a jump to 4D is optional
minorwood.  If opener bids only 3D, then responder's next bid might be
3H.  This would set hearts as trump and the opportunity to ask for
key-cards in diamonds would be lost.
****

=== Both majors

[lavender-box]#Picture bids have priority over kickback#

Otherwise, the first agreed major-suit is trump.

.(a)
[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1S | 2H ||
| 3H | ?  ||
|    | !3S!  || non-serious slam-try for {H}
|    | !3NT! || serious slam-try, high-honour in spades, trump={H}
|    | !4m!  || serious slam-try, trump={H}
|    | 4H    || poor for slam
|    | 4S    || natural, <<#_picture_bids, *picture bid*>>, NF
|===

.(b)
[%autowidth,cols="2*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1C | 1S |
| 2H | 3H |
| ?  |    |
| !3S!   || non-serious slam-try, trump={H}
| !3NT!  || serious slam-try with a high-honour in spades, trump={H}
| !4m!   || serious slam-try, trump={H}
| 4H     || poor for slam
| !4S!   || natural, <<#_picture_bids, *picture bid*>>
|===

For the picture bid, opener will have reversed into a 3-card heart-suit.

To use kickback for hearts in
&(a)& or
&(b)&, responder can
bid 3S (non-serious) then follow with 4S.

