[#_specific_suit_asking]
=== Specific-Suit Asking

Purpose::
   To discover 2nd and 3rd-round controls in a specific suit

[lavender-box]#Used as grand-slam investigation and guarantees that
               all key-cards and the trump-queen are held#

SSA bid = not sign-off, not Q-ask, not K-ask

[%autowidth,cols="2*^,2*<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1D   | !2D! || inverted, GF
| 2S   | !4D! || optional minorwood
| !4S! |  ?   || [ 4S = decline, 0 or 3 ]
|      |  4NT || to play
|      |  5C  || Q ask
|      |  5D  || sign off
|      |  5H || K-ask
|      |  5S  || SSA in {S}
|      |  5NT || SSA in {H} (suit of K-ask)
|      |  6C  || SSA in {C}
|===

==== Responses to SSA

#Treat the ace as a small card because it is known# +
{implies} AQx is the same as Qxx; only 3rd-round control.

Without 2nd-round or 3rd-round control::
   responder signs off in six of the trump suit

@ 6T = no 2nd or 3rd = xxx (or Axx) 

With both 2nd-round and 3rd-round control::
   responder goes above six of the trump suit
   and shows whether the controls are high-card or shortness

@ 6NT = 2nd and 3rd with high-cards
_ = KQ(x) (or AKQ) +

@ 7T = 2nd and 3rd with shortness
_ = x (or stiff A) +

@ other suit above 6T
_ = 2nd with K, 3rd with shortness
_ = Kx tight (or AK tight) +

TIP: 6NT shows that both controls also apply to NoTrump. +
     7T shows that both controls need a trump suit. +
     An in-between response shows one high-card control,
     and one ruffing-control which is necessarily Kx tight.

With only 2nd, or only 3rd::
   the responses depend on number of steps between the SSA bid and 6T

*Two or more intermediate steps:*
(_e.g._ 5S when {D} are trump ) +
@ step 1 = only 3rd-round control,
_ xx (Ax) or Qxx (AQx) +
@ step 2 = only 2nd-round control,
_ Kxx (AKx) +

****
Following a step 1 response, the next step asks if the control
is shortness (xx) or high-card (Qxx). +
The shortness control bids 6T. +
The high-card control bids 6NT.

An only-2nd-round-control must be Kxx so further clarification is
not needed.
****

*One intermediate step:*
(_e.g._ 5NT when {D} are trump ) +
@ step 1 = only 3rd or only 2nd,
_ xx or Qxx or Kxx

*No intermediate steps:*
(_e.g._ 6C when {D} are trump) +
@ above 6T =  3rd-round control

=== Interference

==== Ignore Doubles

We ignore doubles of any asking or telling bids.
_i.e._{thinsp} we bid as though the double did not occur.

==== D0P1 below Five of our Trump-Suit

We show what we have immediately in case there is further
interference.

@ Dbl = 0 +
@ Pass = 1 +
@ 1st step = 2 without Q +
@ 2nd step = 2 with Q +
@ 3rd step = 3 without Q +
@ 4th step = 3 with Q

TIP: The responses are similar to exclusion
     (0, 1, 2{OrLess}, 2{OrMore}, 3{OrLess}, ...)

[lavender-box]#Following pass=1, asker's double is PENALTY; not a
               Q-ask.#

A spare step below five of our-trump-suit is the Q-ask.

If there is no spare-step, then there is no Q-ask.

[%autowidth,cols="4*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
5+^| D0P1 example

| 1S  | (P)  | !4D! | (Dbl) |
| 4NT | (5D) |  ?   ||
|     |      |  Dbl || 0 +
                       > 5H = Q-ask
|     |      |  P   || 1 +
                       > #Dble = penalty# +
                       {emsp}{thinsp}##5H = Q-ask## +
|     |      |  5H  || 2 without Q
|     |      |  5S  || 2 with Q
|     |      |  5NT || 3 without Q
|===

****
When the interference is one step below our trump-suit, then
two-plus-queen is above it.
This is only bad when asker has only one KC, which is unusual;
especially on interference auctions.
****

==== DEPO above Five of our Trump-Suit

@ Dbl = 0 or 2 (#even#) +
@ Pass = 1 (#odd#) +
@ 1st step = 3 without Q +
@ 2nd step = 3 with Q

[lavender-box]#As with D0P1, following pass=1, asker's double is penalty#

